01:23:20.379 --> 01:23:22.505
Something is going on.
I wanna know what it is.

01:23:22.673 --> 01:23:24.132
- Jesus Christ.
- You're not even...

01:23:24.300 --> 01:23:26.551
You're not even looking at me
when you're talking.

01:23:26.719 --> 01:23:30.221
I want you to look at me. Please look
me right in the eyes and just tell me.

01:23:30.473 --> 01:23:34.142
No bullshit. Is there someone else?

01:23:34.310 --> 01:23:35.894
No.

01:23:38.147 --> 01:23:40.023
Have a good trip.

01:23:46.530 --> 01:23:50.200
Our top story this evening
involves Hollywood's three favorite G's.

01:23:50.409 --> 01:23:53.244
A glamorous, glitzy,
gala night on the town.

01:23:53.496 --> 01:23:57.874
It is a who's who of stars,
no IDs necessary. Household names...

01:23:58.083 --> 01:24:00.418
...one and all.
Leeza Gibbons reporting here.

01:24:00.669 --> 01:24:04.380
And right this minute, you could fire
a cannon down Sunset Boulevard...

01:24:04.590 --> 01:24:06.758
...and not come close
to hitting a celebrity.

01:24:06.926 --> 01:24:09.469
Everybody who is anybody is right here...

01:24:09.720 --> 01:24:12.889
...rubbing elbows and making big talk
in this ballroom.

01:24:13.098 --> 01:24:14.599
All the movers, all the shakers.

01:24:14.767 --> 01:24:16.726
Behind the scenes and on the screens.

01:24:17.102 --> 01:24:19.896
We'll leave it to Cher
to wear fire-engine red...

01:24:20.105 --> 01:24:22.315
...when the impossible-to-come-by
invitations...

01:24:22.566 --> 01:24:24.651
...call for black and white only, please.

01:24:24.818 --> 01:24:27.237
- Hello, nice to see you.
- Hi, Teri. Nice to see you.

01:24:27.446 --> 01:24:28.613
- June Gudmundsdottir.
- Hi.

01:24:28.781 --> 01:24:30.198
- Teri Garr. Buck Henry.
- Hello.

01:24:30.366 --> 01:24:31.783
The occasion this evening...

01:24:31.951 --> 01:24:34.285
...just as big and important
as the all-star turnout.

01:24:34.495 --> 01:24:38.414
The studio world-famous for the slogan
"Movies, now more than ever"...

01:24:38.624 --> 01:24:43.002
...is donating prints of 25 of its classic
black-and-white films to the museum.

01:24:43.254 --> 01:24:47.298
Now, they'll be able to say,
"Movies, now more than ever, forever."

01:24:47.508 --> 01:24:48.800
Thank you.

01:24:49.301 --> 01:24:54.639
It's wonderful to see so many
familiar and friendly faces around.

01:24:54.807 --> 01:25:00.144
As you know, the L.A. County Museum
has always been close to our hearts.

01:25:00.354 --> 01:25:03.064
And especially the Motion Department...

01:25:03.232 --> 01:25:05.733
Uh, Motion Picture Department.

01:25:06.986 --> 01:25:10.488
Uh, we're happy to make possible
this donation.

01:25:11.031 --> 01:25:15.618
Now I'd like to introduce the man
whose idea this all was.

01:25:15.828 --> 01:25:17.495
Griffin Mill. Please.

01:25:24.336 --> 01:25:26.337
Thank you, Joel.

01:25:27.131 --> 01:25:28.464
Grab another drink.

01:25:33.012 --> 01:25:35.346
I'd like to extend my thanks...

01:25:35.514 --> 01:25:37.849
...to the patrons of
the Los Angeles County Museum.

01:25:38.684 --> 01:25:41.978
You have long fostered
the art of motion pictures...

01:25:42.187 --> 01:25:46.899
...as a serious and valuable art form
in this community.

01:25:47.151 --> 01:25:49.902
Many people across the country
and around the world...

01:25:50.154 --> 01:25:54.073
...have for too long thought of movies
as a popular entertainment...

01:25:54.325 --> 01:25:56.534
...more than a serious art.

01:25:56.785 --> 01:26:00.913
And I'm afraid a large majority
of the press supports this attitude.

01:26:01.165 --> 01:26:04.876
We want great films
with long shelf lives.

01:26:05.044 --> 01:26:07.503
We want the films
of the new John Hustons...

01:26:07.713 --> 01:26:10.548
...Orson Welles, Frank Capra.

01:26:10.799 --> 01:26:15.887
We and the other major film studios
have a responsibility to the public...

01:26:16.055 --> 01:26:19.932
...to maintain the art
of motion pictures...

01:26:20.184 --> 01:26:22.894
...as our primary mandate.

01:26:23.187 --> 01:26:26.314
Movies are art...

01:26:26.523 --> 01:26:29.734
...now more than ever.

01:26:30.694 --> 01:26:32.111
Thank you.

01:26:39.912 --> 01:26:42.872
Griffin, a hell of a job.
I couldn't have done it better myself.

01:26:43.082 --> 01:26:45.708
I'll know all of your lines soon.

01:26:47.628 --> 01:26:52.048
- Well, are we having fun yet?
- I'm having a great time.

01:26:56.595 --> 01:26:58.429
Yes, I do.

01:26:58.639 --> 01:27:00.556
I did too.

01:27:06.271 --> 01:27:08.856
Is this a friend of a friend?

01:27:09.024 --> 01:27:10.817
- I'm sorry.
- How did you meet?

01:27:10.984 --> 01:27:14.070
How did we meet?
Well, at a funeral. Yes.

01:27:14.279 --> 01:27:16.989
- Isn't that right? Funeral?
- Absolutely. Excuse us.

01:27:17.241 --> 01:27:20.284
Steve. Steve, whose daughter is he with?

01:27:20.452 --> 01:27:21.786
Seriously, I...

01:27:23.163 --> 01:27:25.707
I think she's with his cousin...

01:27:25.874 --> 01:27:28.000
Said he was sure
she was somebody's daughter.

01:27:28.168 --> 01:27:30.920
- I wanna know whose daughter she was.
- No. I don't know.

01:27:52.526 --> 01:27:54.402
BOTH CHUCKLING]

01:27:55.654 --> 01:27:58.656
- Don't make a scene.
- You're doing it all wrong. Ha, ha.

01:27:59.491 --> 01:28:00.700
Here we go.

01:28:00.868 --> 01:28:03.828
Oops. That was a good one.

01:28:04.997 --> 01:28:08.541
Well, that's what I call a real date.

01:28:13.464 --> 01:28:15.339
Should I come in?

01:28:15.716 --> 01:28:17.925
Uh, well...

01:28:18.093 --> 01:28:20.511
- Hmm, well...
- Not tonight.

01:28:20.679 --> 01:28:22.847
- No, not tonight.
- But soon.

01:28:24.183 --> 01:28:26.142
Very soon.

01:28:28.479 --> 01:28:30.688
- How about Mexico?
- Mexico?

01:28:30.939 --> 01:28:32.523
Neutral territory. Acapulco.

01:28:32.733 --> 01:28:34.317
I've never been to Acapulco.

01:28:34.526 --> 01:28:35.735
We'll go.

01:28:35.903 --> 01:28:38.112
- Is that the thing to do?
- That's a thing to do.

01:28:38.280 --> 01:28:40.948
- Let's do it, then.
- We'll go this weekend.

01:28:41.158 --> 01:28:42.700
Really?

01:28:45.370 --> 01:28:48.456
- Do I need a passport?
- Yes.

01:29:37.005 --> 01:29:40.258
Mr. Mill, I'm Detective DeLongpre,
Pasadena Police.

01:29:40.425 --> 01:29:42.093
Yes, I recognize you.

01:29:42.261 --> 01:29:44.554
Did you have a good time
at the party last night?

01:29:44.721 --> 01:29:48.432
No, I didn't. I'm not supposed to
have a good time when I'm on duty.

01:29:48.600 --> 01:29:51.060
Great, well, what do you want,
Detective DeLongpre?

01:29:51.270 --> 01:29:54.105
- I'd like you to come down to the station.
- Why?

01:29:54.314 --> 01:29:56.315
- To look at some pictures.
- Pictures?

01:29:56.567 --> 01:29:59.902
Mug shots.
You know, like in the movies.

01:30:00.070 --> 01:30:02.989
Ah, mug shots. Yes, well, all right.

01:30:03.156 --> 01:30:05.116
- Will you follow me to Pasadena?
- Pasadena.

01:30:05.325 --> 01:30:06.951
- Pasadena.
- Right.

01:30:07.119 --> 01:30:09.787
Will you fasten your safety belt, please?

01:30:13.959 --> 01:30:15.293
- Come, let's go.
- No!

01:30:15.460 --> 01:30:17.461
- Take your hands off her!
- Hush.

01:30:17.671 --> 01:30:19.839
- I want my baby.
- Where's her baby at?

01:30:20.090 --> 01:30:21.883
- Let me go!
- No.

01:30:22.050 --> 01:30:23.968
- Mr. Mill.
- Hello. How are you?

01:30:24.136 --> 01:30:26.220
Good to see you.
Everybody, this is Mr. Mill.

01:30:26.388 --> 01:30:29.974
- Good to see you again.
- He makes movies. Have a seat, Mr. Mill.

01:30:30.392 --> 01:30:33.311
Where the fuck is he going?
Excuse, me, sir. Mr. Mill. Mr. Mill.

01:30:33.520 --> 01:30:35.521
Not in here.
This is my lieutenant's office.

01:30:35.731 --> 01:30:38.691
- Have a seat in my seat. Right here.
- I'm sorry.

01:30:39.192 --> 01:30:40.234
All right, now.

01:30:40.402 --> 01:30:42.653
Uh... Willa.

01:30:42.863 --> 01:30:43.905
- Could you?
- Sorry.

01:30:44.156 --> 01:30:45.865
Your desk. Thank you.

01:30:46.116 --> 01:30:47.491
Sorry. Have a seat, Mr. Mill.

01:30:47.701 --> 01:30:50.077
Listen, um, before we start, I just...

01:30:50.245 --> 01:30:53.247
Paul went to see a movie last night
he came in here raving about.

01:30:53.498 --> 01:30:54.957
What was the name of that movie?

01:30:55.125 --> 01:30:57.668
Changed the lady into a chicken
at the end. What did you see?

01:30:57.836 --> 01:30:59.420
- Freaks.
- Freaks.

01:30:59.671 --> 01:31:01.714
- Have you seen this?
- Tod Browning. Yes.

01:31:01.924 --> 01:31:05.760
"One of us, one of us, one of us,
one of us."

01:31:05.928 --> 01:31:08.179
He came in doing that.
He was raving about it.

01:31:08.388 --> 01:31:12.516
He loved it. He loved it. It was thrilling
for me. Um, Willa. Excuse me.

01:31:12.684 --> 01:31:15.519
Did you happen to see where the tampons
went that were in here?

01:31:15.687 --> 01:31:18.648
- Because I can't seem to find them.
- I didn't take them.

01:31:18.857 --> 01:31:20.149
Who took them? Did he?

01:31:20.359 --> 01:31:22.151
- I don't know. I didn't.
- Who did?

01:31:22.361 --> 01:31:25.196
- I didn't take them.
- You see this? Damn.

01:31:26.531 --> 01:31:29.033
Um, so do you have a break in the case?

01:31:29.242 --> 01:31:31.035
Oh, what makes you say that?

01:31:31.203 --> 01:31:34.038
Well, why else
would you bring me here?

01:31:35.290 --> 01:31:36.415
Why else, indeed.

01:31:37.793 --> 01:31:43.214
Paul. Paul, why have you brought Mr. Mill
in here today?

01:31:43.382 --> 01:31:45.883
- To look at some pictures.
- Willa.

01:31:46.385 --> 01:31:47.927
Pictures?

01:31:48.178 --> 01:31:52.807
Listen, could you...? If you remember,
what were you, uh, wearing that night?

01:31:53.058 --> 01:31:56.894
I was wearing a double-breasted suit,
I believe.

01:31:57.729 --> 01:31:59.563
Oh, it's all right. What's the matter?

01:31:59.731 --> 01:32:02.233
- Mr. Mill, you're so jumpy. Sit down.
- I'll get it.

01:32:02.401 --> 01:32:05.945
No, no, she... That's what she's here for.
It's all right. Have a seat.

01:32:06.196 --> 01:32:07.822
- Sorry.
- No problem.

01:32:08.490 --> 01:32:09.907
Okay.

01:32:10.075 --> 01:32:12.076
Will you take a look at this gentle...?

01:32:12.285 --> 01:32:13.786
- Where were they?
- Right here.

01:32:13.996 --> 01:32:16.497
She found them, look.
You're right. Ha, ha.

01:32:16.748 --> 01:32:19.458
Oh, wait a minute. No, no.
These aren't mine.

01:32:19.626 --> 01:32:21.669
These are slender regular.
These are yours.

01:32:21.837 --> 01:32:23.254
Yeah, I guess you have jumbo.

01:32:24.589 --> 01:32:26.465
Well, I do use jumbo. These are not mine.

01:32:26.842 --> 01:32:29.510
God. Just trying to help you out.

01:32:29.678 --> 01:32:33.305
Um, look, did you see this guy
the night of the murder?

01:32:35.600 --> 01:32:38.019
Sorry, ha, ha. Um...

01:32:38.186 --> 01:32:41.772
No. Uh, you're putting me
in a terrible position here.

01:32:41.940 --> 01:32:43.816
I would hate to get
the wrong person arrested.

01:32:43.984 --> 01:32:47.236
Oh, please. This is Pasadena.
We do not arrest the wrong person.

01:32:47.446 --> 01:32:50.573
That's L.A. See, L.A., they kick
your ass and then they arrest you.

01:32:50.741 --> 01:32:53.409
That's what they do. We don't do that.
Remember last year?

01:32:53.577 --> 01:32:55.953
What was that guy's name?
They put him on the tape.

01:32:56.163 --> 01:32:57.455
- King.
- That's right, King.

01:32:57.664 --> 01:32:59.874
- BLT.
- He was the wrong guy.

01:33:03.128 --> 01:33:05.880
- Do you have a witness?
- Now, I can't answer that.

01:33:06.131 --> 01:33:10.217
Well, either you have a witness
or these are suspects in similar murders.

01:33:10.385 --> 01:33:12.636
Mr. Mill, have you been going
to detective school?

01:33:12.846 --> 01:33:17.224
No, actually, we're doing a movie right
now called The Lonely Room. Scott Glenn...

01:33:17.392 --> 01:33:19.810
...plays a detective like you.
- Is he a black woman?

01:33:20.020 --> 01:33:21.353
- No.
- Don't give me turkey.

01:33:21.521 --> 01:33:25.191
- Lily Tomlin's in that? I heard about that.
- Actually I was drawing a comparison...

01:33:25.400 --> 01:33:27.902
...not based on race or gender.

01:33:28.153 --> 01:33:32.823
Speaking of which,
did you go out with, uh, June, uh...?

01:33:33.700 --> 01:33:34.909
What is that woman's name?

01:33:36.203 --> 01:33:37.411
Gudmundsdottir.

01:33:37.996 --> 01:33:41.749
Ha. What is it? Who? Spell it for me.

01:33:41.917 --> 01:33:44.376
G-U-D-M-U-N-D-S-D-O-T-T-l-R.

01:33:44.586 --> 01:33:46.170
Well, that really helps.

01:33:46.338 --> 01:33:48.422
Could you...?
Uh, did you go out with June...?

01:33:48.590 --> 01:33:50.508
- Gudmundsdottir.
- Yeah. Her. Last night?

01:33:50.675 --> 01:33:51.967
Yes, I did.

01:33:52.135 --> 01:33:53.969
You guys known each other
a long time?

01:33:54.179 --> 01:33:57.181
No, I spoke to her for the first time
the night Kahane was killed.

01:33:57.349 --> 01:33:58.557
Wow.

01:33:58.725 --> 01:34:00.684
- So you didn't know her before this?
- No.

01:34:00.894 --> 01:34:02.520
We met over the phone.

01:34:02.687 --> 01:34:04.688
We got to talking,
one thing led to another.

01:34:04.898 --> 01:34:06.690
You fuck her?

01:34:07.692 --> 01:34:11.529
- What kind of question is that?
- I think it's pretty direct. Did you fuck her?

01:34:12.239 --> 01:34:15.157
I wouldn't answer that question
without a lawyer in the room.

01:34:15.325 --> 01:34:17.701
Then I probably wouldn't
even answer that question.

01:34:17.911 --> 01:34:20.329
Why don't you ask your friend?
He's been following me.

01:34:20.497 --> 01:34:22.623
- He'll probably know.
- All right.

01:34:22.874 --> 01:34:27.878
Paul, did Mr. Mill
fuck June Hudmuuhunta?

01:34:28.088 --> 01:34:29.338
I didn't see him.

01:34:29.506 --> 01:34:32.299
- Got away with it. He didn't see you.
- What are you implying?

01:34:32.467 --> 01:34:35.553
I'm not implying. I asked a direct question.
Did you fuck her?

01:34:35.762 --> 01:34:38.055
I told you I wouldn't answer that
without a lawyer.

01:34:38.223 --> 01:34:41.058
- Why you getting hot under the collar?
- You're being rude.

01:34:41.226 --> 01:34:42.393
Oh, well, excuse me.

01:34:42.602 --> 01:34:46.564
But I think it's kind of soon for her
to be gallivanting in the streets with you.

01:34:46.773 --> 01:34:49.024
I'm there for her as a friend, Miss Avery.

01:34:49.192 --> 01:34:51.360
- Mm.
- Why don't you call her?

01:34:51.570 --> 01:34:54.738
I'm sure she'll be happy to pick over
the horror of what's happened...

01:34:54.906 --> 01:34:58.367
...and tell you how we became friends.

01:34:58.577 --> 01:35:00.202
What is this, fucking Iran?

01:35:00.370 --> 01:35:03.998
Since when does the state tell us how long,
and with whom we can share our grief?

01:35:05.876 --> 01:35:08.002
Or do you hold June Gudmundsdottir...

01:35:08.170 --> 01:35:10.588
...to a special code of conduct
reserved for women?

01:35:17.888 --> 01:35:19.930
What the fuck are you laughing at?

01:35:20.098 --> 01:35:22.266
It's just, just...

01:35:22.434 --> 01:35:24.435
- I'd like to talk to my lawyer.
- Oh, my God.

01:35:24.603 --> 01:35:27.521
DeLONGPRE: "One of us. One of us."
- Can't even say the bitch's name!

01:35:27.689 --> 01:35:31.400
DeLONGPRE:
"One of us. One of us. One of us."

01:35:41.703 --> 01:35:44.121
It's time for you
to get yourself a real good lawyer.

01:35:44.331 --> 01:35:47.541
I had a drink with the guy, Walter.
That's all.

01:35:47.792 --> 01:35:52.922
If you went to Pasadena with the intent
to kill, you could go to the gas chamber.

01:35:53.632 --> 01:35:56.300
I went to Pasadena
with the intent to hire.

01:35:57.052 --> 01:35:58.177
So you say.

01:35:58.345 --> 01:36:01.138
- Griffin, the Schecter brothers are here.
- Griffin. Griffin.

01:36:01.306 --> 01:36:03.224
Griffin. Don't make us wait.

01:36:03.475 --> 01:36:04.642
Who is this man?

01:36:04.809 --> 01:36:06.644
A travel agent called. You're confirmed.

01:36:06.811 --> 01:36:08.145
He grabbed the phone from me.

01:36:08.355 --> 01:36:11.565
- Travel agent?
- I'm going to Puerto Vallarta.

01:36:12.150 --> 01:36:14.652
- You're leaving the country?
- For the weekend.

01:36:14.819 --> 01:36:15.986
It's a risk.

01:36:16.321 --> 01:36:17.571
Why?

01:36:17.822 --> 01:36:20.824
Because Larry Levy
could have my office in three days.

01:36:21.034 --> 01:36:24.495
- That's what Walter thinks.
- You know something I don't know?

01:36:26.831 --> 01:36:27.831
You're pretty smooth.

01:36:28.458 --> 01:36:30.668
I sleep at night.

01:36:31.753 --> 01:36:34.004
- You really should run the studio.
- Tell a friend.

01:36:34.214 --> 01:36:36.840
Yeah, Walter, it's been real.

01:36:37.008 --> 01:36:39.343
Griffin. We're tired of shopping
everything around.

01:36:39.511 --> 01:36:42.930
We wanna go exclusive to one studio.
How much have our three pictures made?

01:36:43.098 --> 01:36:45.224
- $105 million.
- I know some people do better.

01:36:45.392 --> 01:36:47.017
We're consistent and under budget.

01:36:47.185 --> 01:36:49.186
He's not listening. Let's go to Columbia.

01:36:49.354 --> 01:36:52.356
- We already went to Columbia.
- Oh, yeah. What did they say?

01:36:52.524 --> 01:36:53.607
- Bonnie.
- Hey, Bon.

01:36:53.775 --> 01:36:55.693
Hey. I got the Tom Wolfe book.

01:36:56.403 --> 01:36:58.028
Congratulations.

01:36:58.238 --> 01:37:00.864
Bonnie, make him give us a deal.
We want a home.

01:37:01.032 --> 01:37:03.033
We're tired of shopping everything around.

01:37:03.201 --> 01:37:05.494
I thought that's how
you guys like to do business.

01:37:05.704 --> 01:37:07.371
Well, we changed our minds.

01:37:08.623 --> 01:37:09.707
I'll talk to you later.

01:37:11.209 --> 01:37:13.377
Levison says you're
going out of town tomorrow.

01:37:14.045 --> 01:37:15.879
For the weekend.

01:37:16.548 --> 01:37:19.800
Are you going with someone
named June something?

01:37:20.552 --> 01:37:22.136
Yes.

01:37:22.595 --> 01:37:26.932
You took her to a party, Griffin,
with several hundred of my best friends.

01:37:27.142 --> 01:37:29.059
She's recently widowed.

01:37:29.227 --> 01:37:31.645
You weren't in town, so I took her.

01:37:32.897 --> 01:37:35.816
And now you're taking her
to Mexico for the weekend.

01:37:37.527 --> 01:37:39.653
Let's get out of here.
Mom and Dad are fighting.

01:37:39.821 --> 01:37:43.741
Guys, have your lawyer give me a call.

01:37:43.908 --> 01:37:45.909
- You've got a deal.
- Yes!

01:37:46.119 --> 01:37:47.995
Let's get out
before he changes his mind.

01:37:48.163 --> 01:37:49.830
We have witnesses.

01:38:02.844 --> 01:38:04.595
Have a good trip.

01:38:11.603 --> 01:38:14.188
The white zone is for immediate loading...

01:38:14.356 --> 01:38:16.982
...and unloading of passengers only.

01:38:17.192 --> 01:38:18.442
No parking.

01:38:18.651 --> 01:38:24.114
Do not leave your car unattended
due to the current security alert.

01:38:24.324 --> 01:38:28.786
All unattended cars may be towed away
immediately.

01:38:28.953 --> 01:38:30.329
For your safety...

01:38:30.497 --> 01:38:32.498
- Uh, did you bring your passport?
- Yeah.

01:38:32.665 --> 01:38:35.292
You wanna hear something funny?
I forgot mine.

01:38:35.460 --> 01:38:36.543
Oh.

01:38:36.711 --> 01:38:38.962
- We have to go back and get it.
- So stupid of me.

01:38:39.130 --> 01:38:41.673
- We'll miss the plane.
- We'll never make another plane.

01:38:41.841 --> 01:38:43.300
Damn it!

01:38:43.802 --> 01:38:46.136
It's all right.
Anyway, I got a better idea.

01:38:46.304 --> 01:38:48.847
- Do you like the desert?
- I've never been to the desert.

01:38:49.015 --> 01:38:51.141
Never been to the desert?
I know this hideaway...

01:38:51.309 --> 01:38:52.643
...in Desert Hot Springs.

01:38:52.811 --> 01:38:56.480
We'll go there. It's a two-hour drive.
I know the people. We'll call ahead.

01:38:56.648 --> 01:38:58.315
Are we hiding?

01:38:58.525 --> 01:39:01.860
Yeah. Yeah. We're hiding.
We're hiding from everybody.

01:39:03.822 --> 01:39:06.198
You'll like it there.
It'll remind you of Iceland.

01:39:38.857 --> 01:39:43.026
Evening, Mr. M. You're all checked in.
Capone Villa. You know where it is.

01:39:43.236 --> 01:39:45.654
- Yep. Thanks, Walter.
- You're welcome.

01:40:12.682 --> 01:40:15.392
Hey, look.
The water looks like it's steaming.

01:40:15.560 --> 01:40:17.936
Comes out of the ground that way.

01:40:39.918 --> 01:40:42.294
There aren't many people around.

01:40:42.921 --> 01:40:44.963
Well, they're fully booked, actually.

01:40:45.215 --> 01:40:47.257
There's 50 rooms, 100 people.

01:40:47.425 --> 01:40:49.343
Where are they all?

01:40:49.928 --> 01:40:51.637
Hiding.

01:40:51.888 --> 01:40:53.931
Ahem. Sir?

01:40:54.349 --> 01:40:56.475
Couple of Banning Springs water please.

01:40:56.726 --> 01:40:58.435
Right away, Mr. M.

01:41:01.105 --> 01:41:03.524
Do places like this really exist?

01:41:05.109 --> 01:41:06.735
Only in the movies.

01:41:37.475 --> 01:41:40.561
Tell me about the movies you make.

01:41:40.812 --> 01:41:42.479
Why?

01:41:42.981 --> 01:41:47.150
Because I want to know what you do.

01:41:48.152 --> 01:41:53.991
Well, I listen to stories and decide
if they'll make good movies or not.

01:41:54.325 --> 01:41:56.535
I get 125 phone calls a day.

01:41:56.786 --> 01:42:00.372
And if I let that slip to 100...

01:42:00.582 --> 01:42:03.917
...I know I'm not doing my job.

01:42:04.085 --> 01:42:05.502
Oh.

01:42:06.296 --> 01:42:09.590
Everyone that calls,
they wanna know one thing.

01:42:10.383 --> 01:42:13.677
They want me to say yes to them
and make their movie.

01:42:13.928 --> 01:42:16.930
If I say "Yes, I'll make the movie,"
they think come New Years...

01:42:17.098 --> 01:42:21.602
...it's just gonna be them and
Jack Nicholson on the slopes of Aspen.

01:42:22.353 --> 01:42:24.313
That's what they think.

01:42:26.941 --> 01:42:28.692
Problem is...

01:42:28.860 --> 01:42:33.530
...I can only say yes... My studio
can only say yes 12 times a year.

01:42:33.698 --> 01:42:38.368
And collectively,
we hear about 50,000 stories a year.

01:42:38.578 --> 01:42:40.537
So it's hard.

01:42:42.874 --> 01:42:45.751
And I guess sometimes I'm not nice...

01:42:47.253 --> 01:42:49.254
...and make enemies.

01:42:50.715 --> 01:42:53.216
And that's what I was to David.

01:42:54.052 --> 01:42:55.636
Enemy.

01:42:56.387 --> 01:42:58.972
Was his story one of the 12?

01:42:59.223 --> 01:43:01.058
No, it wasn't.

01:43:01.726 --> 01:43:02.934
Why?

01:43:03.144 --> 01:43:07.856
It lacks certain elements that we need
to market a film successfully.

01:43:08.399 --> 01:43:10.442
What elements?

01:43:12.570 --> 01:43:17.574
Suspense, laughter, violence.

01:43:19.369 --> 01:43:21.745
Hope, heart.

01:43:24.082 --> 01:43:26.500
Nudity, sex.

01:43:28.086 --> 01:43:29.586
Happy endings.

01:43:31.172 --> 01:43:33.799
Mainly happy endings.

01:43:37.095 --> 01:43:38.929
What about reality?

01:43:40.640 --> 01:43:42.516
You're not from Iceland, are you?

01:43:44.477 --> 01:43:46.436
Did I say that?

01:43:47.563 --> 01:43:48.855
Hmm.

01:43:49.774 --> 01:43:53.777
Why don't you put me in the hot springs
and see if I melt?

01:44:42.034 --> 01:44:43.577
I love you.

01:44:43.828 --> 01:44:47.748
I know. I know.

01:44:55.173 --> 01:44:57.257
I know.

01:44:57.884 --> 01:44:59.843
There's something you have to know.

01:45:00.011 --> 01:45:02.888
- I love you. I know I love you.
- Something I have to tell you.

01:45:03.055 --> 01:45:04.973
That's all I need.

01:45:05.183 --> 01:45:06.725
Nothing can change that.

01:45:06.976 --> 01:45:08.393
June.

01:45:08.603 --> 01:45:10.353
- David's death.
- No. Shh.

01:45:10.521 --> 01:45:12.397
It's in the past.

01:45:12.607 --> 01:45:15.609
Don't. Don't. It's another life.

01:45:15.860 --> 01:45:18.862
I have to tell you something.
Something you have to know.

01:45:19.071 --> 01:45:22.991
Don't, don't, don't say anymore. Don't.

01:45:23.367 --> 01:45:25.410
- I was responsible.
- I love you. Don't.

01:45:25.620 --> 01:45:28.705
- It was my fault.
- Don't say that.

01:45:28.915 --> 01:45:32.876
Don't, don't, don't. I love you.

01:46:51.289 --> 01:46:52.497
Mr. M?

01:46:52.874 --> 01:46:54.749
Mr. M, sorry to disturb you.

01:46:54.917 --> 01:46:57.168
There's a telephone call
and it sounds important.

01:46:57.336 --> 01:46:59.212
- Who is it?
- A Mr. Dick Mellen.

01:46:59.380 --> 01:47:01.339
He says he's your lawyer.

01:47:23.154 --> 01:47:24.738
Dick, how'd you fine me?

01:47:24.947 --> 01:47:28.158
Come on, Griff.
Who the hell do you think you're talking to?

01:47:28.326 --> 01:47:29.993
Yeah. What's going on?

01:47:30.202 --> 01:47:33.496
- Levison's out.
- Out?

01:47:33.664 --> 01:47:35.874
They gave him six hours
to clean out his office.

01:47:36.083 --> 01:47:38.168
- Who's taking over?
- Nothing's been decided.

01:47:38.336 --> 01:47:41.671
All we know is Reggie Goldman
went home with the clap or something.

01:47:42.590 --> 01:47:46.301
- Listen, am I in a position to...?
- I don't wanna talk about studio politics.

01:47:46.469 --> 01:47:48.720
Why didn't you tell me about this
Kahane business?

01:47:50.181 --> 01:47:51.723
Kahane.

01:47:51.933 --> 01:47:53.391
I tried to, Dick, but...

01:47:53.601 --> 01:47:55.226
You didn't try hard enough.

01:47:55.394 --> 01:47:58.396
You better be at the Pasadena
Police Station in about four hours.

01:47:59.815 --> 01:48:02.192
Pasadena? What for?

01:48:02.401 --> 01:48:05.320
A fucking lineup, that's what for.

01:48:05.488 --> 01:48:06.863
They got a witness, evidently.

01:48:07.073 --> 01:48:09.699
Now, look, I found you a guy,
his name is Gar Girard.

01:48:09.867 --> 01:48:12.535
He's a top-flight criminal lawyer.
He's tough, hard-nosed.

01:48:12.703 --> 01:48:15.455
Don't you talk to anybody else.
Just get there.

01:48:16.207 --> 01:48:19.876
- I'll be there.
- Griffin, this is a tough one.

01:48:20.086 --> 01:48:21.419
Good luck.

01:48:22.964 --> 01:48:24.589
Thanks.

01:48:32.974 --> 01:48:37.394
Mr. Mill, the studio's very upset
about the publicity this might generate.

01:48:37.561 --> 01:48:40.438
But I'll handle the press, the police,
the judge and the witness.

01:48:40.606 --> 01:48:43.066
Mr. Mill. Thank you for coming down
without a fight.

01:48:43.234 --> 01:48:45.819
It's in your best interest.
You sleep in that suit?

01:48:45.987 --> 01:48:47.946
Get away from that woman.
She's the enemy.

01:48:48.114 --> 01:48:50.490
- Follow me.
- Susan, I had a lovely time at the Mint.

01:48:50.658 --> 01:48:52.242
I can't believe you remembered it.

01:48:52.451 --> 01:48:54.786
Mr. Mill, Gar Girard.
I'm here to represent you.

01:48:54.996 --> 01:48:57.622
Dick Mellen called me in on this.
Here's the situation.

01:48:57.832 --> 01:49:00.250
They've got a witness.
They want you to do a lineup.

01:49:00.418 --> 01:49:02.544
If you say no, they'll arrest you.

01:49:02.753 --> 01:49:05.588
And even if you get identified,
I'll get you off on bail.

01:49:05.798 --> 01:49:09.592
Now, this witness lives across the street
from the parking lot.

01:49:09.760 --> 01:49:12.679
Even if she makes an identification,
a positive ID right now...

01:49:12.888 --> 01:49:16.975
...even if that happens, it was very late
at night. By the time I'm finished with her...

01:49:17.143 --> 01:49:20.603
...the world will have a new legal
standard for blindness. Keep the faith...

01:49:20.813 --> 01:49:23.314
This is just like they do it on television.

01:49:23.524 --> 01:49:25.608
Excuse me, Susan. Good luck.

01:49:25.818 --> 01:49:29.029
You don't have to worry.
You can see them but they can't see you.

01:49:29.280 --> 01:49:31.197
- Fine. Fine.
- Just tell the truth.

01:49:31.407 --> 01:49:35.869
Oh, I will. Because
I saw him clearly. There's no problem.

01:49:37.413 --> 01:49:39.372
All right, Allen. Fire it up.

01:49:39.582 --> 01:49:41.791
Number 1, step forward.

01:49:42.084 --> 01:49:44.794
Make a quarter turn to the right.

01:49:45.504 --> 01:49:48.006
- Are those prescription glasses?
- You can't ask her that.

01:49:48.174 --> 01:49:49.883
- Fine.
- It's very hard, you know.

01:49:50.092 --> 01:49:52.927
- Oh, yeah. I know.
- Number 2, take one step forward.

01:49:53.137 --> 01:49:56.306
- I wouldn't wanna pick the wrong one.
- No. God forbid.

01:49:56.849 --> 01:49:58.141
You just take your time.

01:49:58.309 --> 01:50:01.352
Oh, I know.
Anybody look, uh, vaguely familiar?

01:50:01.562 --> 01:50:03.146
Take a quarter turn to the left.

01:50:05.066 --> 01:50:06.816
- Face forward.
- Take your time.

01:50:06.984 --> 01:50:09.235
Step back into position.
Number 3, take one step.

01:50:09.403 --> 01:50:10.987
- This is not easy.
- I know.

01:50:11.155 --> 01:50:13.406
- It never is.
- I mean, I am trying.

01:50:13.616 --> 01:50:15.366
Yes. Just take your time.

01:50:15.534 --> 01:50:17.869
- And I did see him clearly.
- Face forward.

01:50:18.037 --> 01:50:19.329
Make a quarter turn to the left.

01:50:22.875 --> 01:50:25.168
- Step back as...
- No, no, no. I don't know.

01:50:25.419 --> 01:50:26.711
- Well.
- Look hard.

01:50:26.921 --> 01:50:31.382
- Look really... Take a good look.
- No. I did, I did, I am. Um...

01:50:31.592 --> 01:50:33.802
Could I see, um...

01:50:34.762 --> 01:50:36.721
...Number 3 again?
- Call Number 3.

01:50:36.931 --> 01:50:38.973
- Wait a minute, wait a minute.
- Um, could I...?

01:50:39.183 --> 01:50:41.476
- Could she call her own numbers?
- Excuse me.

01:50:41.685 --> 01:50:45.313
- Maybe she wants to see again.
- Number 5, take one step forward.

01:50:45.481 --> 01:50:46.815
- Listen...
- Excuse me.

01:50:46.982 --> 01:50:48.066
Number 5.

01:50:48.275 --> 01:50:50.860
Susan, I think she can call
who she's interested in.

01:50:51.028 --> 01:50:54.781
- You're absolutely right.
- No, the other one. That one.

01:50:54.949 --> 01:50:56.533
- By the number.
- Which one?

01:50:56.700 --> 01:51:00.286
- Oh, um, uh, it's not Number 6.
- Not Number 6.

01:51:00.454 --> 01:51:02.080
- How about Number 5?
- Three.

01:51:02.289 --> 01:51:04.207
- Three.
- What do you mean, Number 3?

01:51:04.375 --> 01:51:06.709
- She can request who she wants.
- Just a second.

01:51:06.877 --> 01:51:08.419
You wanna see what number?

01:51:08.587 --> 01:51:12.632
Him! That's him.
I'd swear on my mother's grave.

01:51:12.842 --> 01:51:15.218
Number 3.
I think we're concluded, Ms. Avery.

01:51:15.386 --> 01:51:17.887
- The one, Number 3.
- Number 3. On her mother's grave.

01:51:18.055 --> 01:51:19.556
- Yes.
- Number 3?

01:51:20.057 --> 01:51:21.975
Number 3.
I think we heard what she said.

01:51:22.184 --> 01:51:24.727
- Yeah, I would say so.
- Okay, Doug, take them out.

01:51:24.895 --> 01:51:27.814
- Number 3, thank you.
- Just relax. You're in a chair.

01:51:28.482 --> 01:51:30.525
- Ma'am, may I be personal?
- Yes.

01:51:30.693 --> 01:51:32.443
Where the fuck is your mother buried?

01:51:33.821 --> 01:51:36.239
- Let's get out of here.
- Let's get out of this sauna.

01:51:41.245 --> 01:51:44.831
I don't know who got to that witness,
but she sure wrapped up my case.

01:51:45.040 --> 01:51:47.917
- You're a lucky man, Mr. Mill.
- Goddamn it, no ramp again.

01:51:48.127 --> 01:51:49.502
Witnesses can't be relied on.

01:51:49.712 --> 01:51:53.047
Remember Witness for the Prosecution,
Marlene Dietrich and Tyrone Power?

01:51:53.257 --> 01:51:55.842
That's it. You're free as a bird.
No witness, no crime.

01:51:56.051 --> 01:51:58.553
That Avery woman thinks
you just got away with murder.

01:51:58.721 --> 01:52:01.014
Everybody does, Mr. Mill.

01:52:48.437 --> 01:52:53.191
Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed by thy name.

01:52:53.400 --> 01:52:58.238
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.

01:52:58.697 --> 01:53:01.950
Give us this day our daily bread...

01:53:02.159 --> 01:53:05.078
...and forgive us our trespasses...

01:54:43.635 --> 01:54:47.638
You've made a wonderful movie.
It's perfect.

01:54:47.848 --> 01:54:50.641
It's Oscar time, Larry.

01:54:55.731 --> 01:54:58.691
- What?
- We're too late. Come on.

01:54:58.901 --> 01:55:01.194
I gotta get the door open.

01:55:02.571 --> 01:55:04.072
Come on.

01:55:07.326 --> 01:55:09.619
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Get back!

01:55:27.846 --> 01:55:31.057
Oh. What took you so long?

01:55:31.266 --> 01:55:32.725
Traffic was a bitch.

01:55:43.320 --> 01:55:44.654
It's outstanding.

01:55:44.863 --> 01:55:48.282
- The audience is gonna love it.
- You sold it out.

01:55:48.450 --> 01:55:51.994
How could you let him sell you out?
What about truth? What about reality?

01:55:52.162 --> 01:55:54.914
What about the way
the old ending tested in Canoga Park?

01:55:55.124 --> 01:55:56.457
Everybody hated it.

01:55:56.667 --> 01:55:59.669
We reshot it. Now everybody loves it.
That's reality.

01:55:59.837 --> 01:56:02.630
You had an ending which was true.
You didn't give it a chance.

01:56:02.798 --> 01:56:06.217
Who is this person? Does she know
anything about working with grown-ups?

01:56:06.427 --> 01:56:08.594
Bonnie, goddamn it, goddamn it.

01:56:08.804 --> 01:56:11.764
This is a hit.
This is what we're here for.

01:56:11.974 --> 01:56:14.016
Yeah, well, it didn't have
to end this way.

01:56:14.226 --> 01:56:17.520
- I want you out of here.
- Good thinking, Larry.

01:56:17.729 --> 01:56:19.730
I'm going over your head, Larry.

01:56:19.940 --> 01:56:22.233
Bonnie, you're fired.

01:56:23.944 --> 01:56:25.278
Fuck you.

01:56:25.487 --> 01:56:28.281
It takes more to make it
in this business than a dirty mouth.

01:56:28.449 --> 01:56:30.324
The campaign.

01:56:52.431 --> 01:56:53.764
Two points.

01:56:59.062 --> 01:57:01.314
Celia, it's important.
I need to talk to him now.

01:57:01.523 --> 01:57:03.274
- No, Bonnie, he's very busy.
- Please.

01:57:03.442 --> 01:57:05.443
- No, you... Bonnie.
- Please, it's me, Bonnie.

01:57:05.652 --> 01:57:07.862
- We're friends.
- Bonnie, you don't understand.

01:57:08.071 --> 01:57:12.742
- I am not just me, I'm also the job.
- Please. Please. Please.

01:57:12.951 --> 01:57:17.955
Oh, honey. All right, all right.
I'll try, okay?

01:57:20.417 --> 01:57:22.335
Three points.

01:57:22.711 --> 01:57:26.297
- Great shot.
- Oh, Walter, stop that nonsense.

01:57:26.507 --> 01:57:29.258
Griffin, it's Bonnie.

01:57:29.468 --> 01:57:31.302
She's here.

01:57:33.222 --> 01:57:35.223
Great shot.

01:57:35.933 --> 01:57:37.058
Levy fired her?

01:57:37.267 --> 01:57:39.685
Yes, sir. I guess he did.

01:57:41.188 --> 01:57:43.272
Well, I can't see her now.

01:57:43.732 --> 01:57:46.025
I promised I'd be home early.

01:57:47.319 --> 01:57:48.736
Tell her I'll get back to her.

01:57:48.946 --> 01:57:51.489
Walter, get your foot
off the fucking couch.

01:57:51.698 --> 01:57:52.782
Tell her yourself.

01:57:52.950 --> 01:57:55.952
- Yes. Okay, well, could you hold, please?
- Griffin. Griffin.

01:57:56.119 --> 01:57:57.203
I have to talk to you.

01:57:57.412 --> 01:57:58.746
- Please!
- It's very important.

01:57:58.914 --> 01:58:02.833
- Griffin, please. Can we talk about it?
- Bonnie, you'll land on your feet. I know it.

01:58:03.001 --> 01:58:05.878
- You're a survivor.
- It's Larry Levy's office. It's important.

01:58:06.088 --> 01:58:08.089
Oh, put it in the front seat.

01:58:08.423 --> 01:58:10.967
Give it a minute and
transfer it to the car phone.

01:58:23.438 --> 01:58:26.482
- Yeah?
- Griffin, I have Larry Levy on the line.

01:58:26.650 --> 01:58:29.026
Larry, how'd the screening go?
How's my new ending?

01:58:29.194 --> 01:58:31.737
Fantastic. Fantastic.
Worked like gangbusters.

01:58:31.947 --> 01:58:35.908
- That's why you get the big bucks, Griff.
- Yeah, yeah. Stop kissing my ass, Larry.

01:58:36.118 --> 01:58:38.995
- What? Can't this wait?
- I don't think it should. This is hot.

01:58:39.162 --> 01:58:41.497
I got a writer who's got a pitch
you ought to hear.

01:58:41.665 --> 01:58:44.000
It's something we should go for.
It's a great idea.

01:58:44.167 --> 01:58:47.670
- Yeah? Who's the writer?
- I'll put him on the speaker. Hold on.

01:58:47.838 --> 01:58:49.463
Hi, Griff. Remember me?

01:58:49.631 --> 01:58:52.967
I'm the asshole who used to be
in the postcard business.

01:58:53.176 --> 01:58:54.802
- You?
- Yeah, that's right.

01:58:55.012 --> 01:58:57.471
The king of suspense himself.
You remember me?

01:58:57.681 --> 01:58:59.515
I haven't heard from you in a while.

01:58:59.725 --> 01:59:02.184
Well, I've been busy.
I've been writing a script.

01:59:02.352 --> 01:59:04.061
- I got inspired.
- Give him the pitch.

01:59:04.271 --> 01:59:06.230
You'll love this, Griffin. It's great.

01:59:06.440 --> 01:59:09.191
All right, it's a Hollywood story,
Griff. A real thriller.

01:59:09.401 --> 01:59:12.695
It's about a shit-bag producer
studio exec...

01:59:12.863 --> 01:59:16.240
